Create a DB first as in the previous section!

- If you get an error like: **Ledger does not have entry**, ****the node is not configured as archival (see above), or the indexer data needs to be deleted 
first in the database table.
- Itâ€™s best practice to start a fresh node as archival and start the indexer immediately afterwards.


cd /usr/local/bin/algorand-indexer_linux_amd64_2.10.0
#Check
./algorand-indexer daemon -h

#Start indexer in write mode to populate DB
./algorand-indexer daemon -P "host=localhost port=5432 user=postgres password=postgres dbname=indexer" --algod=/mnt/algorand

/usr/local/bin/algorand-indexer_linux_amd64_2.10.0/algorand-indexer daemon -P "host=localhost port=5432 user=postgres password=postgres dbname=indexer" --algod=/mnt/algorand

#Start the indexer in read-only, e.g. to prevent the postgres from becoming larger
#This allows providing the REST API still
./algorand-indexer daemon -P "host=localhost port=5432 user=postgres password=postgres dbname=indexer"  --no-algod
